TITLE: Echo Server using Stream Piping in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: An optimized HTTP echo server that uses Node.js streams to efficiently pipe request data directly to the response. This demonstrates the power of Node.js streams for handling data transfer without buffering the entire request.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/modules/anatomy-of-an-http-transaction.md#2025-04-21_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const http = require('node:http');

http
  .createServer((request, response) => {
    if (request.method === 'POST' && request.url === '/echo') {
      request.pipe(response);
    } else {
      response.statusCode = 404;
      response.end();
    }
  })
  .listen(8080);
```

