TITLE: Using async/await with try/catch for Promise Error Handling in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates error handling for Promises using async/await syntax with a try/catch block. This approach allows for more synchronous-looking code while still properly catching and handling asynchronous errors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/asynchronous-work/discover-promises-in-nodejs.md#2025-04-21_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
async function performTask() {
  try {
    const result = await myPromise;
    console.log(result);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error); // Handles any errors
  } finally {
    // This code is executed regardless of failure
    console.log('performTask() completed');
  }
}

performTask();
```

