TITLE: Configuring GitHub Actions for npm Publishing - YAML
DESCRIPTION: This snippet configures GitHub Actions for automatic publishing of a Node.js package to npm when a new tag is pushed. It checks out the repository, sets up Node.js using a specified version file, and installs dependencies using npm ci.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/typescript/publishing-a-ts-package.md#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: YAML
CODE:
```
# This is mostly boilerplate.

name: Publish to npm
on:
  push:
    tags:
      - '**@*'

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    permissions:
      contents: read
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version-file: '.nvmrc'
          registry-url: 'https://registry.npmjs.org'
      - run: npm ci

      # - name: Publish to npm
      #   run: â€¦ npm publish â€¦
```

