TITLE: Incorrect Mixing of Blocking and Non-Blocking Operations
DESCRIPTION: This example shows a problematic pattern where blocking and non-blocking operations are mixed incorrectly. The synchronous fs.unlinkSync() may execute before the asynchronous fs.readFile() completes, potentially causing issues.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/asynchronous-work/overview-of-blocking-vs-non-blocking.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const fs = require('node:fs');

fs.readFile('/file.md', (err, data) => {
  if (err) throw err;
  console.log(data);
});
fs.unlinkSync('/file.md');
```

