TITLE: Demonstrating Synchronous Callback Issues in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: This example illustrates a potential issue with synchronous callbacks in asynchronous-looking functions, where variables may not be initialized as expected.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/asynchronous-work/event-loop-timers-and-nexttick.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let bar;

// this has an asynchronous signature, but calls callback synchronously
function someAsyncApiCall(callback) {
  callback();
}

// the callback is called before `someAsyncApiCall` completes.
someAsyncApiCall(() => {
  // since someAsyncApiCall hasn't completed, bar hasn't been assigned any value
  console.log('bar', bar); // undefined
});

bar = 1;
```

