TITLE: Implementing AbortSignal with Child Process in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use AbortSignal with child_process.spawn() to control process termination. The AbortController can be used to stop the process with an AbortError.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v15.5.0.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const controller = new AbortController();
const { signal } = controller;
const grep = spawn('grep', ['ssh'], { signal });
grep.on('error', err => {
  // This will be called with err being an AbortError if the controller aborts
});
controller.abort(); // stops the process
```

