TITLE: Using process.getBuiltinModule() in ES Modules for Environment-Aware Code
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to conditionally load Node.js built-in modules in code that may run in other environments. It safely checks for Node.js presence and uses the new process.getBuiltinModule() API to load the 'fs' module and create a require function for user modules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v20.16.0.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: mjs
CODE:
```
if (globalThis.process?.getBuiltinModule) {
  // Run in Node.js, use the Node.js fs module.
  const fs = globalThis.process.getBuiltinModule('fs');
  // If `require()` is needed to load user-modules, use createRequire()
  const module = globalThis.process.getBuiltinModule('module');
  const require = module.createRequire(import.meta.url);
  const foo = require('foo');
}
```

