TITLE: Major Version Changes - Node.js Core Modules
DESCRIPTION: Collection of major version changes affecting Node.js core functionality including modifications to assert, buffer, crypto, dns, fs, http, stream and other essential modules. These changes introduce breaking changes that require attention when upgrading Node.js versions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v18.0.0.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
- assert,util: compare RegExp.lastIndex while using deep equal checks
- buffer: refactor byteLength to remove outdated optimizations
- buffer: expose Blob as a global
- buffer: graduate Blob from experimental
- crypto: cleanup validation
- dns: remove dns.lookup and dnsPromises.lookup options type coercion
- http: refactor headersTimeout and requestTimeout logic
- stream: remove thenable support
- worker: expose BroadcastChannel as a global
```

