TITLE: Demonstrating Readline Promise API Usage in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates the basic use of the new readline module's Promise API. It creates an interface for reading input, asks a question, and logs the response.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v17.0.0.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import * as readline from 'node:readline/promises';
import { stdin as input, stdout as output } from 'process';

const rl = readline.createInterface({ input, output });

const answer = await rl.question('What do you think of Node.js? ');

console.log(`Thank you for your valuable feedback: ${answer}`);

rl.close();
```

