TITLE: Implementing Promise.try() for Error Handling in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the use of Promise.try() to handle both synchronous and asynchronous errors consistently. The function mightThrow() is wrapped in Promise.try(), allowing errors to be caught in a .catch() block regardless of whether they occur synchronously or asynchronously.
