TITLE: TCP Client Connection (MJS)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to set up a TCP client in Node.js using the 'net' module. The client connects to a server on localhost:8080, sends a greeting, and logs data received. Handles server disconnection with an 'end' event listener.
