TITLE: Domain Error Propagation Limitations
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the limitations of error propagation across nested domains, showing how errors cannot properly bubble up through multiple domain layers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/community/domain-postmortem.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const d1 = domain.create();
d1.foo = true; // custom member to make more visible in console
d1.on('error', er => {
  /* handle error */
});

d1.run(() =>
  setTimeout(() => {
    const d2 = domain.create();
    d2.bar = 43;
    d2.on('error', er => console.error(er.message, domain._stack));
    d2.run(() => {
      setTimeout(() => {
        setTimeout(() => {
          throw new Error('outer');
        });
        throw new Error('inner');
      });
    });
  })
);
```

