TITLE: Using the zlib.crc32() Function for Checksum Calculation
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the newly exposed zlib.crc32() function which computes a 32-bit Cyclic Redundancy Check checksum of data. The function can use a previous checksum value as a starting point for incremental checksums and supports both string and Buffer inputs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v20.15.0.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const zlib = require('node:zlib');
const { Buffer } = require('node:buffer');

let crc = zlib.crc32('hello'); // 907060870
crc = zlib.crc32('world', crc); // 4192936109

crc = zlib.crc32(Buffer.from('hello', 'utf16le')); // 1427272415
crc = zlib.crc32(Buffer.from('world', 'utf16le'), crc); // 4150509955
```

