TITLE: Mocking object method with Node.js test runner
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use the `node:test` module to mock a method of an object during testing. It defines an object with a method, then uses `t.mock.method` to spy on the method. It then asserts the mocked method is called and that its return value is as expected.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v19.1.0.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
test('spies on an object method', t => {
  const number = {
    value: 5,
    add(a) {
      return this.value + a;
    },
  };
  t.mock.method(number, 'add');

  assert.strictEqual(number.add(3), 8);
  assert.strictEqual(number.add.mock.calls.length, 1);
});
```

