TITLE: Using util.promisify to Open a File - CommonJS
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use util.promisify to convert fs.open into a promise-based function, allowing for the use of async/await syntax.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/manipulating-files/working-with-file-descriptors-in-nodejs.md#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const fs = require('node:fs');
const util = require('node:util');

async function example() {
  const open = util.promisify(fs.open);
  const fd = await open('/Users/joe/test.txt', 'r');
}
example();
```

