TITLE: Broken Socket Server Implementation in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: An example showing incorrect stream handling that will cause the socket to remain paused forever in Node.js v0.10+. This code fails to properly consume the data stream.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/feature/streams2.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// WARNING! BROKEN!
net.createServer(function(socket) {
  // we add an 'end' method, but never consume the data
  socket.on('end', function() {
    // It will never get here.
    socket.end('I got your message (but didnt read it)\n');
  });
}).listen(1337);
```

