TITLE: Handling Readable Events in Node.js Streams (MJS)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the use of the 'readable' event to manually control data flow from a stream. Requires 'MyStream' to be defined. Sets 'highWaterMark' to 1 for finer control over data chunks, which are logged after conversion to a string format. Handles end of stream with an 'end' event listener.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/modules/how-to-use-streams.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: mjs
CODE:
```
const stream = new MyStream({
  highWaterMark: 1,
});

stream.on('readable', () => {
  console.count('>> readable event');
  let chunk;
  while ((chunk = stream.read()) !== null) {
    console.log(chunk.toString()); // Process the chunk
  }
});
stream.on('end', () => console.log('>> end event'));
```

