TITLE: Using --experimental-default-type Flag in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: The `--experimental-default-type` flag allows users to switch the default module system in Node.js. It enables files that would typically be interpreted as CommonJS to be treated as ES modules based on specific file extensions and input types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v20.10.0.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
The new flag `--experimental-default-type` can be used to flip the default
module system used by Node.js. Input that is already explicitly defined as ES
modules or CommonJS, such as by a `package.json` `"type"` field or `.mjs`/`.cjs`
file extension or the `--input-type` flag, is unaffected.
```

