TITLE: Emitting Events from Constructors using process.nextTick() in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to properly emit events from within a constructor using process.nextTick(), ensuring that event listeners have been set up before the event is emitted.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/asynchronous-work/event-loop-timers-and-nexttick.md#2025-04-21_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const EventEmitter = require('node:events');

class MyEmitter extends EventEmitter {
  constructor() {
    super();

    // use nextTick to emit the event once a handler is assigned
    process.nextTick(() => {
      this.emit('event');
    });
  }
}

const myEmitter = new MyEmitter();
myEmitter.on('event', () => {
  console.log('an event occurred!');
});
```

