TITLE: Proper Sequential Non-Blocking Operations with Callbacks
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the correct way to sequence non-blocking operations using nested callbacks. It ensures that the file is only deleted after it has been read, while maintaining a fully non-blocking execution pattern.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/asynchronous-work/overview-of-blocking-vs-non-blocking.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const fs = require('node:fs');

fs.readFile('/file.md', (readFileErr, data) => {
  if (readFileErr) throw readFileErr;
  console.log(data);
  fs.unlink('/file.md', unlinkErr => {
    if (unlinkErr) throw unlinkErr;
  });
});
```

