TITLE: Improving HTTP Keep-Alive Socket Handling in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: This change ensures that when using keep-alive Agent, the socket waits for both prefinish and end events before reuse, preventing parser errors from premature writing of the next request.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v6.2.2.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
When freeing the socket to be reused in keep-alive Agent wait for both prefinish and end events. Otherwise the next request may be written before the previous one has finished sending the body, leading to parser errors.
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Test Framework Arrow Function Conversion
DESCRIPTION: Modernization of test suite code by converting traditional function callbacks to arrow function syntax in test files for improved readability and consistency.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v11.4.0.md#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// Changed from:
test('description', function() { /* ... */ });
// To:
test('description', () => { /* ... */ });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Adding Flush Option in fs.writeFile
DESCRIPTION: Introduces a 'flush' option in the fs.writeFile family of functions to ensure data is immediately written to permanent storage, preventing potential stale data reads.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v20.10.0.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
This allows subsequent read operations to see stale data.
This PR adds a 'flush' option to the `fs.writeFile` family of functions which
forces the data to be flushed at the end of a successful write operation.
```

