TITLE: HTTP Get Request with Numeric Authentication Vulnerability Example
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a security vulnerability where using numeric values for authentication in HTTP get requests could create uninitialized buffers. This code example shows the problematic pattern that was fixed in Node.js 4.x release line.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/vulnerability/july-2017-security-releases.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const opts = require('url').parse('http://127.0.0.1:8180');
opts.auth = 1e3; // A number here triggers the bug
require('http').get(opts, res => res.pipe(process.stdout));
```

