TITLE: Using Object.values and Object.entries Methods in JavaScript (ES2017)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the new Object.values and Object.entries static methods introduced in ES2017. These methods complement Object.keys and return arrays of property values or key-value pairs respectively.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/announcements/update-v8-5.4.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const obj = {
  x: 0,
  y: 100,
};

const keys = Object.keys(obj); // ['x', 'y']
const values = Object.values(obj); // [0, 100]
const entries = Object.entries(obj); // [['x', 0], ['y', 100]]
```

