TITLE: Styling Console Output in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the styleText function from the node:util module to add color and formatting to console output. This feature is noted as being in 'Active development' for Node.js version 22.11.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/command-line/output-to-the-command-line-using-nodejs.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { styleText } from 'node:util';
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const { styleText } = require('node:util');
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
console.log(
  styleText(['red'], 'This is red text ') +
    styleText(['green', 'bold'], 'and this is green bold text ') +
    'this is normal text'
);
```

