TITLE: Demonstrating Domain Module Cross-Module Exception Handling
DESCRIPTION: Shows how one module's domain can unexpectedly affect exception handling in another module, potentially silencing errors without the originator's knowledge.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/community/domain-postmortem.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// module a.js
const b = require('./b');
const c = require('./c');

// module b.js
const d = require('domain').create();
d.on('error', () => {
  /* silence everything */
});
d.enter();

// module c.js
const dep = require('some-dep');
dep.method(); // Uh-oh! This method doesn't actually exist.
```

