TITLE: Known Issues in Node.js v4.2.2
DESCRIPTION: Documentation of existing bugs and issues that are still present in this release, including REPL freezing, DNS query crashes, and URL resolution problems.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v4.2.2.md#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: Markdown
CODE:
```
- Surrogate pair in REPL can freeze terminal. [#690](https://github.com/nodejs/node/issues/690)
- Calling `dns.setServers()` while a DNS query is in progress can cause the process to crash on a failed assertion. [#894](https://github.com/nodejs/node/issues/894)
- `url.resolve` may transfer the auth portion of the url when resolving between two full hosts, see [#1435](https://github.com/nodejs/node/issues/1435).
```

