TITLE: Managing Multiple Projects with Shared Dependencies in npm 1.0
DESCRIPTION: Workflow example demonstrating how to install a package globally, link it to multiple local projects, and update all instances at once by updating the global package.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/npm/npm-1-0-link.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
npm install express -g  # install express globally
cd ~/dev/js/my-blog     # development folder one
npm link express        # link the global express into ./node_modules
cd ~/dev/js/photo-site  # other project folder
npm link express        # link express into here, as well

                        # time passes
                        # TJ releases some new stuff.
                        # you want this new stuff.

npm update express -g   # update the global install.
                        # this also updates my project folders.

```

