TITLE: NAPI String Value Function Vulnerability
DESCRIPTION: Functions napi_get_value_string_latin1(), napi_get_value_string_utf8(), and napi_get_value_string_utf16() contain a buffer overflow vulnerability when called with non-NULL buf and bufsize of 0. Affects Node.js versions 10.x, 12.x, and 14.x.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/vulnerability/june-2020-security-releases.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: cpp
CODE:
```
napi_get_value_string_latin1()
napi_get_value_string_utf8()
napi_get_value_string_utf16()
```

