TITLE: Opening a File with Callback - CommonJS
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to open a file for reading using the callback style in CommonJS format. It utilizes the fs.open method to retrieve the file descriptor.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/manipulating-files/working-with-file-descriptors-in-nodejs.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const fs = require('node:fs');

fs.open('/Users/joe/test.txt', 'r', (err, fd) => {
  // fd is our file descriptor
});
```

