TITLE: Converting Anonymous Closures to Arrow Functions in Node.js Tests
DESCRIPTION: This pattern appears in multiple commits where contributors are modernizing the Node.js test suite by replacing traditional anonymous closure functions with arrow functions for cleaner syntax and improved maintainability.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v10.15.1.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// Before conversion (typical pattern being replaced):
function() {
  // test code
}

// After conversion (new pattern being implemented):
() => {
  // test code
}
```

