TITLE: Publishing Data with Diagnostics Channel in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of creating a named diagnostics channel and publishing data to it. This code demonstrates how to publish MySQL query information through a diagnostics channel for monitoring and debugging purposes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v15.1.0.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const dc = require('diagnostics_channel');
const channel = dc.channel('mysql.query');

MySQL.prototype.query = function query(queryString, values, callback) {
  // Broadcast query information whenever a query is made
  channel.publish({
    query: queryString,
    host: this.hostname,
  });

  this.doQuery(queryString, values, callback);
};
```

