TITLE: TCP Server with Duplex Streams (MJS)
DESCRIPTION: Describes a node TCP server using the 'net' module, which sends a greeting to clients and logs incoming data. Utilizes socket event listeners for data reception and client disconnection. Listens on port 8080.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/modules/how-to-use-streams.md#2025-04-21_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: mjs
CODE:
```
import { net } from 'node:net';

// Create a TCP server
const server = net.createServer(socket => {
  socket.write('Hello from server!\n');

  socket.on('data', data => {
    console.log(`Client says: ${data.toString()}`);
  });

  // Handle client disconnection
  socket.on('end', () => {
    console.log('Client disconnected');
  });
});

// Start the server on port 8080
server.listen(8080, () => {
  console.log('Server listening on port 8080');
});
```

