TITLE: Authenticating Users via Express.js Route - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This Express.js route for user authentication retrieves username and password, performs basic sanitization, and compares the hash of the provided password with the stored hash using a secure timing-safe comparison. The operation is synchronous, potentially causing delays in handling concurrent requests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/getting-started/profiling.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
app.get('/auth', (req, res) => {
  let username = req.query.username || '';
  const password = req.query.password || '';

  username = username.replace(/[!@#$%^&*]/g, '');

  if (!username || !password || !users[username]) {
    return res.sendStatus(400);
  }

  const { salt, hash } = users[username];
  const encryptHash = crypto.pbkdf2Sync(password, salt, 10000, 512, 'sha512');

  if (crypto.timingSafeEqual(hash, encryptHash)) {
    res.sendStatus(200);
  } else {
    res.sendStatus(401);
  }
});
```

