TITLE: Creating a basic HTTP server using Node.js (CommonJS)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a basic HTTP server in Node.js using the CommonJS module system. It imports the `createServer` function from the `http` module, defines a hostname and port, and creates a server that responds with 'Hello World' to all requests. The server listens on the specified hostname and port, logging a message to the console when it starts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/tr/about/index.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: cjs
CODE:
```
const { createServer } = require('node:http');

const hostname = '127.0.0.1';
const port = 3000;

const server = createServer((req, res) => {
  res.statusCode = 200;
  res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/plain');
  res.end('Hello World');
});

server.listen(port, hostname, () => {
  console.log(`Server running at http://${hostname}:${port}/`);
});
```

