TITLE: Adding New User via Express.js Route - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This Express.js route snippet handles adding a new user by accepting username and password as query parameters. It sanitizes the username, checks the validity, generates a secure salt and hashed password using the crypto library, and stores the data if the username is valid and unique.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/getting-started/profiling.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
app.get('/newUser', (req, res) => {
  let username = req.query.username || '';
  const password = req.query.password || '';

  username = username.replace(/[!@#$%^&*]/g, '');

  if (!username || !password || users[username]) {
    return res.sendStatus(400);
  }

  const salt = crypto.randomBytes(128).toString('base64');
  const hash = crypto.pbkdf2Sync(password, salt, 10000, 512, 'sha512');

  users[username] = { salt, hash };

  res.sendStatus(200);
});
```

