TITLE: Checking V8 Heap Size Limit in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the v8 module to check the current heap size limit of the V8 engine. The code calculates and displays the maximum heap size in gigabytes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/diagnostics/memory/understanding-and-tuning-memory.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: cjs
CODE:
```
const v8 = require('node:v8');
const { heap_size_limit } = v8.getHeapStatistics();
const heapSizeInGB = heap_size_limit / (1024 * 1024 * 1024);

console.log(`${heapSizeInGB} GB`);
```

