DESCRIPTION: This snippet represents a commit where string concatenation is replaced with template literals in JavaScript code. Template literals provide a more readable and maintainable way to construct strings, especially when including variables. This conversion is a common practice in modern JavaScript development to enhance code clarity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v8.9.2.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

