TITLE: Getting information from a path (CommonJS)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates extracting the directory name, base name, and extension from a given file path using the `path.dirname()`, `path.basename()`, and `path.extname()` methods in a CommonJS (CJS) Node.js environment. It showcases how to dissect a file path into its constituent parts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/manipulating-files/nodejs-file-paths.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: cjs
CODE:
```
const path = require('node:path');

const notes = '/users/joe/notes.txt';

path.dirname(notes); // /users/joe
path.basename(notes); // notes.txt
path.extname(notes); // .txt
```

