TITLE: Demonstrating Prototype Pollution in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates prototype pollution by modifying the __proto__ property through JSON parsing. It shows how this can lead to unexpected behavior and potential Denial of Service (DoS) attacks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/getting-started/security-best-practices.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const a = { a: 1, b: 2 };
const data = JSON.parse('{"__proto__": { "polluted": true}}');

const c = Object.assign({}, a, data);
console.log(c.polluted); // true

// Potential DoS
const data2 = JSON.parse('{"__proto__": null}');
const d = Object.assign(a, data2);
d.hasOwnProperty('b'); // Uncaught TypeError: d.hasOwnProperty is not a function
```

