TITLE: REDOS Vulnerable Path Validation Example
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a vulnerable regular expression that could cause REDOS attacks when validating file paths. The regexp contains a doubly-nested quantifier that can cause exponential matching time.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/asynchronous-work/dont-block-the-event-loop.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
app.get('/redos-me', (req, res) => {
  let filePath = req.query.filePath;

  // REDOS
  if (filePath.match((\/\.+)+$/)) {
    console.log('valid path');
  } else {
    console.log('invalid path');
  }

  res.sendStatus(200);
});
```

