TITLE: Generating Bash Completion Scripts for Node.js CLI
DESCRIPTION: Introduces the ability to generate a bash completion script for the Node.js binary using the command `node --completion-bash`, allowing users to enhance their command-line experience with auto-completion.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v10.12.0.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Markdown
CODE:
```
- **cli**
  - Added bash completion for the `node` binary. To generate a bash completion
    script, run `node --completion-bash`. The output can be saved to a file
    which can be sourced to enable completion. [#20713](https://github.com/nodejs/node/pull/20713)
```

