TITLE: Filtering Node.js Internal Functions from perf Output
DESCRIPTION: This sed command filters out Node.js and V8 internal functions from the perf output file, making the resulting flame graph easier to read by focusing on user code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/diagnostics/flame-graphs.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
sed -i -r \
  -e "/( __libc_start| LazyCompile | v8::internal::| Builtin:| Stub:| LoadIC:|\[unknown\]| LoadPolymorphicIC:)/d" \
  -e 's/ LazyCompile:[*~]?/ /' \
  perfs.out
```

