TITLE: Demonstrating Callback Hell in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates the problem of 'callback hell' where multiple nested asynchronous functions create code that is difficult to read and maintain.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/asynchronous-work/asynchronous-flow-control.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
async1(function (input, result1) {
  async2(function (result2) {
    async3(function (result3) {
      async4(function (result4) {
        async5(function (output) {
          // do something with output
        });
      });
    });
  });
});
```

