TITLE: Problematic Readable Stream Implementation That Ignores Backpressure
DESCRIPTION: Example of a poorly implemented custom Readable stream that ignores the return value from .push(), which can break backpressure signaling from the destination stream.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/learn/modules/backpressuring-in-streams.md#2025-04-21_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// This is problematic as it completely ignores the return value from the push
// which may be a signal for backpressure from the destination stream!
class MyReadable extends Readable {
  _read(size) {
    let chunk;
    while (null !== (chunk = getNextChunk())) {
      this.push(chunk);
    }
  }
}
```

