TITLE: Fixing Argument Order in Assertions - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet addresses the problem of incorrect argument order in the 'assert.strictEqual' assertions, which can lead to misleading failure messages and affect the reliability of the tests. By standardizing the argument order to (actual, expected), it ensures consistency across test cases.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v10.15.1.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Fixing argument order in assertions
assert.strictEqual(actual, expected);

```

