TITLE: Enhancing Node.js Memory Management
DESCRIPTION: These changes improve Node.js memory management by notifying V8 of low memory conditions, adding allocation checks, and implementing overflow detection in malloc operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nodejs/nodejs.org/blob/main/apps/site/pages/en/blog/release/v6.12.1.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: C++
CODE:
```
src**: notify V8 for low memory when alloc fails (Anna Henningsen) [#8482](https://github.com/nodejs/node/pull/8482)
```

LANGUAGE: C++
CODE:
```
src**: provide allocation + nullptr check shortcuts (Anna Henningsen) [#8482](https://github.com/nodejs/node/pull/8482)
```

LANGUAGE: C++
CODE:
```
src**: pass desired return type to allocators (Anna Henningsen) [#8482](https://github.com/nodejs/node/pull/8482)
```

LANGUAGE: C++
CODE:
```
src**: add Malloc() size param + overflow detection (Anna Henningsen) [#8482](https://github.com/nodejs/node/pull/8482)
```

